            {
                "s2_paper_id": "6b165afea6c8ff466348eb1104169f91113efc14",
                "title": "Homological stability for Hurwitz spaces and the Cohen-Lenstra conjecture over function fields",
                "year": 2009,
                "venue": "",
                "citation_count": 165,
                "reference_count": 69,
                "abstract": "We prove a homological stabilization theorem for Hurwitz spaces: moduli spaces of branched covers of the complex projective line. This has the following arithmetic consequence: let \u2018 > 2 be prime and A a nite abelian \u2018-group. Then there exists Q = Q(A) such that, for q greater than Q, a positive fraction of quadratic extensions of Fq(t) have the \u2018-part of their class group isomorphic to A.",
