            {
                "s2_paper_id": "5364609eddb97de2fdb7ab365f140996404dc462",
                "title": "String homology of spheres and projective spaces",
                "year": 2006,
                "venue": "",
                "citation_count": 30,
                "reference_count": 18,
                "abstract": "We study a spectral sequence that computes the (mod 2) S^1-equivariant homology of the free loop space LM of a manifold M (the \"string homology\" of M). Using it and knowledge of the string topology operations on the homology of LM, we compute the string homology of M when M is a sphere or a projective space.",
                "authors": [
                    {
                        "s2_author_id": "100530245",
                        "name": "Craig Westerland"
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "s2_paper_id": "d21d993ab1c24fce9b48284dbe55890c4837dde4",
                "title": "Equivariant operads, string topology, and Tate cohomology",
                "year": 2006,
                "venue": "",
                "citation_count": 12,
                "reference_count": 33,
                "abstract": "From an operad $$\\fancyscript {C}$$ with an action of a group G, we construct new operads using the homotopy fixed point and orbit spectra. These new operads are shown to be equivalent when the generalized G-Tate cohomology of $$\\fancyscript {C}$$ is trivial. Applying this theory to the little disk operad $$\\fancyscript {C}_2$$ (which is an S1-operad) we obtain variations on Getzler\u2019s gravity operad, which we show governs the Chas\u2013Sullivan string bracket.",
